## Asbury University is a Christian liberal arts university in the Wesleyan-Holiness tradition. Our commitment to academic excellence and spiritual vitality spans more than 130 years. Asbury is a place where faith is deepened, minds are challenged and servant leaders are developed.

## Our Mission

The mission of Asbury University is to provide an academically challenging, spiritually vibrant and socially relevant education that prepares graduates to engage their cultures and advance the cause of Christ around the world.

## Our Vision

Asbury University will be a leading Christ-centered university that equips men and women through academic excellence and spiritual vitality for lifelong learning, leadership and service to the professions, society, the family and the Church, thereby preparing them to engage their cultures and advance the cause of Christ around the world.

## Our Core Values

Asbury University is a community called to:

- Academic Excellence – We believe in the pursuit of knowledge under the lordship of Jesus Christ, the integration of Christian faith and learning, and the development of wisdom and character.
- Spiritual Vitality – We believe in the necessity of a personal relationship with Jesus Christ, the transforming power of the Holy Spirit, and the cultivation of biblical holiness in all of life.
- Stewardship – We believe in the faithful management of all resources entrusted to us by God, including time, talents, finances, the environment and our physical bodies.
- Servant Leadership – We believe in the development of leaders who serve with integrity, humility, courage and grace.
- Authentic Community – We believe in the dignity of all persons, the development of meaningful relationships, and the practice of mutual accountability.

## Our History

Asbury University was founded in 1890 as a Christian liberal arts university in the Wesleyan-Holiness tradition. Our commitment to academic excellence and spiritual vitality spans more than 130 years. Asbury is a place where faith is deepened, minds are challenged and servant leaders are developed.

## Our Location

Asbury University is located in Wilmore, Kentucky, a small town in the heart of the Bluegrass region. Wilmore is a safe, friendly community with a strong sense of history and tradition. The campus is situated on 400 acres of rolling hills, with easy access to Lexington, Louisville and Cincinnati.

## Our Accreditation

Asbury University is accredited by the Southern Association of Colleges and Schools Commission on Colleges (SACSCOC) to award associate, baccalaureate, and master’s degrees. Asbury University also holds accreditation from the Association for Biblical Higher Education (ABHE) and the National Association of Schools of Music (NASM).

## Our Academic Programs

Asbury University offers more than 50 undergraduate majors and minors, as well as graduate programs in education, business, and ministry. Our academic programs are designed to prepare students for a lifetime of learning, leadership, and service.

## Our Spiritual Life

Asbury University is committed to fostering a vibrant spiritual life on campus. We offer a variety of opportunities for worship, prayer, and spiritual growth, including chapel services, small groups, and mission trips. Our students are encouraged to develop a personal relationship with Jesus Christ and to live out their faith in all areas of life.

## Our Student Life

Asbury University offers a rich and vibrant student life experience. Our students participate in a wide range of activities, including athletics, music, theater, and student government. We also offer a variety of clubs and organizations, as well as opportunities for service and leadership.

## Our Alumni

Asbury University has a strong and active alumni network. Our graduates are making a difference in their professions, their communities, and the world. They are leaders in business, education, ministry, and many other fields.

## Our Future

Asbury University is committed to continuing its tradition of academic excellence and spiritual vitality. We are investing in new programs, facilities, and technologies to prepare our students for the challenges and opportunities of the 21st century. We are also expanding our global reach, with partnerships and programs around the world.

## Why Choose Asbury University?

Asbury University is a unique place where faith and learning come together. We offer a challenging academic environment, a vibrant spiritual life, and a supportive community. Our graduates are prepared to make a difference in the world.

If you are looking for a Christ-centered university that will challenge you academically, spiritually, and personally, then Asbury University is the place for you.
